# Repo workflow: branches, commits, PRs

Details: **`docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md`** (sections 4–6).

## Protected `master`
- Never push directly to `master`. All changes go through a PR.
- If changes were accidentally committed on `master`, create a branch from HEAD and open a PR (do not rewrite history).

## Branching
- Always branch off the latest `master`:
  - `git switch master && git pull --ff-only`
  - `git switch -c <branch>`
- Naming:
  - `feat/<topic>`
  - `fix/<topic>`
  - `refactor/<topic>`
  - `docs/<topic>`
  - `chore/<topic>`

## PR cadence
- Prefer **1 PR per milestone/iteration** that is reviewable end-to-end.
- If the diff gets too large, split into 2 PRs within the same topic (still milestone-scoped).
- Draft PR is OK as soon as the branch is pushed; keep committing into the same PR.

## Commit guidance
- Keep commits review-friendly. Prefer 1–3 commits per PR:
  - backend + tests
  - frontend
  - docs/tooling
- Commit messages should capture intent (why), not file lists.

## AI / Cursor efficiency
- Keep prompts **scoped**; use **Handoff** + `03` ACTIVE; minimal `@` context. See **`docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md` § 10** and **`.cursor/rules/ai-cursor-efficiency.mdc`**.

## Proposed PR block (assistant output format)
When ready for PR, provide:
- base: `master`
- head: `<branch>`
- title: short, scoped
- summary: 1–3 bullets
- test plan: exact commands run
- notes: invariants (e.g. no behavior change) + checks to watch

## Optional automation (human or trusted environment)
- End-of-iteration (gates + push + PR + merge): `scripts/iter-end.ps1` / `scripts/iter-end.sh`. Details: **`docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md` § 6b**.
- Scripts: `scripts/gh-pr-push-merge.ps1` (Windows) and `scripts/gh-pr-push-merge.sh` (Unix). Details: **`docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md` § 6a** (`-BodyFile` / `pr-body.md`).
- **GitHub CLI:** one-time `gh auth login` + `gh auth setup-git` → persistent on Windows (Credential Manager). See **`docs/DEVELOPMENT_WORKFLOW.md` § 6**.
- Optional token file: copy **`.env.example`** → **`.env`** (gitignored), set `GH_TOKEN` — never commit secrets.
- Merge automation only works if `gh` is authenticated and repo rules allow merge (no blocking required reviews).

